{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 20:05:23.889048", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and goals\\n- Detect anomalies\\n- Localize faulty devices\\n- Identify root causes\\n- No mitigation actions proposed\\n\\nHigh-level health assessment\\n- Underlay routing: OSPF adjacencies are established and stable across all core, distribution, and server-access routers. Neighbor states are Full on all links checked.\\n- IP reachability: Hosts in multiple access subnets can reach the server farm network (10.200.0.0/24) with low latency and 0% packet loss in sampled pings.\\n- Server ports: DNS server is listening on 10.200.0.2:53; load balancer and web servers are listening on TCP/80 as expected.\\n- DHCP: Hosts are receiving IPs and default gateways correctly; lease durations are short (lab default).\\n\\nObserved anomalies\\n1) DNS resolution failure from subnet 10.2.1.0/24\\n- Symptom:\\n  - On host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.13), DNS lookups for local names (web99.local, web0.local) time out:\\n    - getent hosts web99.local; getent hosts web0.local: timed out\\n    - curl http://web99.local and http://web0.local: total ~5.0s with namelookup/connect/starttransfer all 0.000000, indicating DNS failure/timeout.\\n  - The same host successfully accesses services by IP:\\n    - curl http://10.200.0.7 (load balancer): completes in ~1.1s\\n    - curl http://10.200.0.3 (web_server_0): completes in ~1.1s\\n  - Hosts in other subnets (e.g., host_1_1_1_1 in 10.1.1.0/24) resolve and access web99.local and web0.local normally (lookups fast, total ~1.0–1.1s).\\n\\n- Evidence:\\n  - host_2_1_1_1 resolv.conf contains nameserver 8.8.8.8 (external), not the internal DNS 10.200.0.2.\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 resolv.conf contains nameserver 10.200.0.2, and resolution works.\\n  - DHCP server configuration (dhcpd.conf):\\n    - subnet 10.2.1.0 declares option domain-name-servers 8.8.8.8\\n    - all other subnets point to 10.200.0.2 for DNS\\n  - Connectivity to the internal DNS server (10.200.0.2) from 10.2.1.0/24 hosts is fine (ping OK), so this is not a reachability issue.\\n  - DNS server is listening on 10.200.0.2:53 (TCP) and loopback, indicating service is up.\\n\\n- Impact:\\n  - Hosts in the 10.2.1.0/24 subnet fail to resolve local enterprise zone names (*.local), including web99.local and web0.local, despite having full L3 reachability to the server farm. Users must use IPs to reach services; name-based access fails.\\n\\n2) No evidence of routing or server-side service failure\\n- OSPF neighbors across core, dist, and server-access routers are Full and stable.\\n- All web servers and the load balancer are listening on TCP/80 (0.0.0.0:80).\\n- DNS server is operational and reachable from multiple subnets.\\n- Sample pings between hosts and to server farm IPs show low latency and no loss.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- The fault is localized to the DHCP configuration for subnet 10.2.1.0/24 on dhcp_server.\\n- Specifically, the DHCP option domain-name-servers setting is incorrect for this subnet only.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Misconfiguration on dhcp_server: subnet 10.2.1.0 is configured with option domain-name-servers 8.8.8.8 instead of the internal DNS server 10.200.0.2. This causes clients in that subnet to query an external resolver that has no knowledge of the internal zone, leading to name resolution timeouts/failures for local services.\\n\\nAdditional notes\\n- The lab shows short DHCP lease times (default-lease-time 30; max-lease-time 60;). This appears to be lab-specific and not problematic here.\\n- Design constraint stating backend web servers should not be directly accessible from hosts is not contradicted by these tests; we validated front-end services (web0.local and web99.local). Direct access to backends behind the load balancer was not observed or required for this diagnosis., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='09acc8c2-19fe-42b0-9015-c237cc1374ec'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
